name: "TMJ #7" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Ink on paper with digital embellishments.] This piece is an abstract with simulated symbology. You could call it faux-asemic writing---if you were familiar with asemic writing and wanted to apply that concept to this image. You could also call it a sigil that was created by a computer program. Chaos computing, if you will... Or if you won't. It does what it wants! ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
